25 militants killed in S. Afghanistan: official
Security forces eliminated 25 Taliban militants in their former stronghold Nad Ali district of southern Helmand province, a local official said Sunday."A group of Taliban rebels were meeting in a house in Nad Ali district Saturday evening when troops raided the house, killing 25 insurgents including commander Mullah Rahmatullah," district police chief Asmatullah Sadat told Xinhua.However, he did not provide more details.Taliban militants have yet to make comment.Nad Ali, a former bastion of Taliban militants in south Afghanistan was captured by Afghan and NATO-led troops last February.